label.value: radioisotope assay evidence

value.value: A type of direct assay evidence resulting from the assessment of biological reactions by use of a radioactive isotope to label the reactant.

label.value: radioimmunoassay evidence

value.value: A type of protein detection assay evidence resulting from the use of a radioligand to measure the binding of a substance to a specific antibody or other receptor system.

label.value: resonant mirror biosensor evidence

value.value: A type of direct assay evidence from the analysis of the real-time interaction between an analyte in solution and its interactant linked to the surface of the resonant mirror.

label.value: restriction fragment detection evidence

value.value: A type of DNA detection assay evidence resulting from homologous DNA fragments digested by restriction enzymes, and the resulting restriction fragments are sorted by length to illustrate differences.

label.value: spectrophotometry evidence

value.value: A type of spectrometry evidence resulting from the evaluation of a molecule in a fluid or solid by its ability to alter the transmission of light at specific wavelengths.

label.value: surface plasmon resonance evidence

value.value: A type of physical interaction evidence based on real-time, rapid plasmon generation on the interface between a planar surface and vacuum that measures changes in refractive index close to the sensor surface when an analyte and its immobilized ligand bind to observe and characterize molecular interaction.

definition.value: Plasmons are generated by an incident light beam.

label.value: syngeneic transplantation experiment evidence

value.value: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence resulting from a transplantation in which the transplanted material (stem cells) is from an individual's identical twin.

label.value: TACE activity assay evidence

value.value: A type of enzymatic activity assay evidence resulting from the analysis of tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-a converting enzyme (TACE), which releases a soluble TNF-a from the membrane-bound precursor protein.

label.value: tissue microarray evidence

value.value: A type of cytochemistry evidence resulting from the analysis of section(s) of a paraffin block containing embedded tissues cores arranged in an array pattern.

label.value: transgenic organism evidence

value.value: A type of genetic transformation evidence resulting from an organism that has had its expressed phenotype altered by modification.

label.value: tryptic phosphopeptide mapping assay evidence

value.value: A type of mass spectrometry evidence resulting from the analysis of prepared phosphopeptides separated in two dimensions on a TLC plate.

label.value: terminal deoxynucleotidyl transferase dUTP nick end labeling assay evidence

value.value: A type of apoptotic assay evidence resulting from the visualization of DNA fragmentation by detection of exposed 3'-OH ends, localized by terminal deoxynucleotidyl transferase (TdT) which then catalyzes the addition of labeled dUTPs.

label.value: urine test evidence

value.value: A type of direct assay evidence resulting from the analysis of a urine sample.

label.value: WST-1 assay evidence

value.value: A type of cell proliferation assay evidence resulting from the assessment of metabolic activity from a water-soluble tetrazolium salt WST-1 being reduced outside the cell (by reacting with mitochondrial succinate-tetrazolium reductase) to form a formazan dye.

label.value: xenotransplantation phenotypic evidence

value.value: A type of anatomical perturbation phenotypic evidence resulting from the transplantation, implantation, or infusion of live cells, tissues, or organs between individuals of different species.
